aVIn 1339, Ambrogio Lorenzetti finished a monumental commission
p56
aVin the governing council chamber of Siena's Palazzo Pubblico.
p57
aVIt's a painting that speaks to us, even screams to us, today.
p58
aV"Art is a lie that makes us realize truth,"
p59
aVPablo Picasso once said.
p60
aVAnd as we search for the truth about government,
p61
aVwe should keep Ambrogio's work,
p62
aVnot a lie but an allegory, in our collective mind's eye.
