aa(lp64
VDuring Lorenzetti's time,
p65
aVthe political legitimacy of Italian city-states
p66
aVwas often on very shaky ground.
p67
aVSiena was a republic,
p68
aVbut there had been enormous unrest
p69
aVin the two decades leading up to the commission.
p70
aVSiena's political leaders, who would literally govern
p71
aVunder the eyes of these allegorical figures,
p72
aVwere Lorenzetti's intended audience.
p73
aVHe was cataloging the obligations
p74
aVof the governing to the governed.
